         xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
         xml:id="atomviz.import.xyz" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"
         xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
         xmlns:ns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <title>XYZ files</title>

  <para>OVITO can import XYZ text files written by several simulation
  packages. The XYZ format is a simple column-based format, which is
  documented <link
  xlink:href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XYZ_file_format">here</link>.</para>

  <note>
    <para>The XYZ format does not store any simulation box dimensions. OVITO
    just takes the axis-aligned bounding box of all atoms found in the file as
    the simulation box. Note that this can lead to problems with systems with
    periodic boundary conditions, where the exact simulation cell dimensions
    are important.</para>
  </note>

  <para>Compressed files (having a <filename>.gz</filename> suffix) are
  automatically decompressed on the fly.</para>
</section>
